org.ofbiz.core.entity.jdbc.interceptors

Interface SQLInterceptorFactory

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    LoggingSQLInterceptorFactory, NoopSQLInterceptorFactory

    public interface SQLInterceptorFactory
    SQLInterceptorFactory is responsible for generating SQLInterceptors when asked.

    An instance of this class will be loaded from THE class path resource called "ofbiz-database.properties" and must have public no-arges constructor.

    The factory is responsible for giving out SQLInterceptors. Its these objects that are used as call backs for each SQL statement that is executed. An SQLInterceptor is asked for for every new SQL statement. So its up to the factory to decide whether to allocate a new one, re-use them or make them stateless. But remember that new gen allocation is blindingly fast, so the suggestion is to allocate a new one every time.
